projects.name: Marketplace Fulfillment Platform
projects.description: Manages the entire lifecycle of third-party seller orders on the Amazon marketplace, from initial ingestion and payment verification to shipment tracking and final delivery confirmation. This project tracks bugs, feature requests, and operational tasks related to order processing, inventory management, and customer communication.

project_components.name: Order Ingestion
project_components.description: Handles the initial intake of new orders from the Amazon API and creation of internal records.

project_components.name: Payment Verification
project_components.description: Component for processing payments, handling verification flags, and managing refunds.

project_components.name: Shipment & Logistics
project_components.description: Manages shipping label generation, carrier integration, and shipment status tracking.

project_components.name: Inventory Sync
project_components.description: Synchronizes stock levels between our internal system and seller accounts on Amazon.

project_components.name: Customer Notifications
project_components.description: Responsible for sending automated emails and updates to buyers regarding their order status.

project_versions.name: v1.2 'Orion'
project_versions.description: Initial platform launch with core order processing and fulfillment features for the US marketplace.

project_versions.name: v1.3 'Pegasus'
project_versions.description: Introduces improved payment verification logic and adds support for new shipping carriers.

project_versions.name: v2.0 'Andromeda'
project_versions.description: Major platform overhaul with a new UI, enhanced reporting, and a public API for sellers.

labels.name: payment-verification
labels.description: Tasks related to orders flagged for manual payment review or verification.

labels.name: shipping-discrepancy
labels.description: Issues where shipment status or quantities do not match order records.

labels.name: unshipped-item
labels.description: Tracking for items within an order that have not yet been shipped, especially in partial shipments.

labels.name: api-sync-error
labels.description: Relates to data inconsistencies caused by issues with the Amazon Seller Central API connection.

labels.name: customer-inquiry
labels.description: An issue prompted by a direct communication or escalation from a buyer.

labels.name: missing-data
labels.description: An order record is missing critical information, such as line items.

issue_types.name: Task
issue_types.description: A standard task that needs to be completed by the operations team.

issue_types.name: Bug
issue_types.description: A problem in the system causing incorrect data or behavior in order processing.

issue_statuses.name: To Do
issue_statuses.description: The issue is in the backlog, waiting for an operator to pick it up.

issue_statuses.name: In Progress
issue_statuses.description: This issue is being actively investigated or worked on at the moment.

issue_statuses.name: In Review
issue_statuses.description: The action is complete and is awaiting verification from a senior operator or manager.

issue_statuses.name: Done
issue_statuses.description: The issue has been resolved and no further action is required.

issue_statuses.name: Blocked
issue_statuses.description: This issue cannot be progressed due to an external dependency, such as waiting on the customer.

issue_priorities.name: Highest
issue_priorities.description: This issue represents a critical failure (e.g., data loss, major outage) and must be resolved immediately.

issue_priorities.name: High
issue_priorities.description: This issue impacts a significant number of orders or revenue and should be addressed urgently.

issue_priorities.name: Medium
issue_priorities.description: This issue is a standard operational task with a normal priority level.

issue_priorities.name: Low
issue_priorities.description: This issue is of low priority and can be addressed when time permits.

issue_resolutions.name: Fixed
issue_resolutions.description: A resolution has been implemented and the issue is considered resolved.

issue_resolutions.name: Won't Fix
issue_resolutions.description: The issue was reviewed and a decision was made not to implement a fix.

issue_resolutions.name: Duplicate
issue_resolutions.description: The issue is a duplicate of another existing issue in the system.

issue_resolutions.name: Incomplete
issue_resolutions.description: There is not enough information to investigate or resolve the issue.

issue_resolutions.name: Cannot Reproduce
issue_resolutions.description: The reported problem could not be reproduced by the team.

comments.body: Fulfillment team is checking warehouse logs for SKU-936959-209. There might be a stock discrepancy.
This looks like a potential API sync issue. Checking the carrier's tracking information against our shipment records.
The ingestion service may have failed to process the item list. Manually triggering a data refresh for this order.
Contacting the payments team to review the transaction details in our PayPal portal.
The remaining two units are on backorder. ETA is three business days. I'll draft a notification for the customer.
Warehouse confirms no shipment was created. The order status was updated in error. Reverting status to 'Unshipped' and prioritizing.
Payment flag has been cleared. Fulfillment is confirming stock for the last dresser before shipping.
The PayPal transaction has been approved. Now investigating the shipment issue. Looks like a data sync error.
This is a mess. It seems OI-374960 and OI-730524 shipped, but OI-329627 is still pending. Consolidating the tracking info now.
The Gift Card was processed correctly on Amazon's end. Clearing the flag internally. API sync initiated for missing items.
The remaining items are scheduled to ship tomorrow. Customer has already been notified via automated email.
Confirmed status: Three partial shipments created. The unshipped item (Roku Ultra) is out of stock. Contacting buyer about a refund for that item.
Carrier confirmed they have the package. Our system's shipped quantity data is stale. Forcing an update now.
The bank transfer has been confirmed and the verification flag is cleared. The shipment issue appears to be a data sync error.
The dining table is a large-item shipment and will be dispatched next week via a different carrier. Adding notes to the order.
Payment has been confirmed as collected by the carrier. The missing unit was a warehouse error; processing a refund for it now.
Manual data refresh was successful. Item details are now populated.
API sync complete. Order items are now visible in the system.
The PayPal transaction was flagged for a billing address mismatch but has now been manually approved by our team.
The remaining two units are in a separate package with a different tracking number. Linking it to the order now.
Data refresh from API was successful. The order item is now correctly displayed.

dashboards.name: Daily Fulfillment Operations
dashboards.description: Real-time overview of today's orders, shipping status, and any outstanding payment verifications or discrepancies requiring manual intervention.

dashboards.name: Payment Verification Queue
dashboards.description: A focused view of all orders currently flagged for manual payment verification, sorted by order value and age.

filters.name: Orders Requiring Action
filters.description: A filter to show all issues that are not in 'Done' status and require manual intervention, such as payment holds or shipping discrepancies.

filters.name: High-Value Orders with Payment Flags
filters.description: Shows all open issues with the 'payment-verification' label where the order total is greater than $1000.

filters.name: Unshipped & Overdue
filters.description: All issues related to orders that are still unshipped after their promised ship date has passed.

fields.name: Amazon Order ID
fields.description: Custom field to store the primary Amazon Order ID (e.g., 112-xxxxxxx-xxxxxxx).

fields.name: Seller Order ID
fields.description: Custom field to store the seller-specific order identifier (e.g., SO-xxxxxx).

fields.name: Root Cause
fields.description: A dropdown field to categorize the source of an issue (e.g., API Error, Warehouse Error, Payment Gateway).

field_configurations.description: Default field configuration for the Marketplace Fulfillment Platform project.
Configuration for Bug issue types, making the 'Root Cause' field mandatory on resolution.

workflows.name: MFP Default Workflow
workflows.description: Standard workflow for handling operational tasks and bugs related to order fulfillment.

workflow_statuses.name: Open
workflow_statuses.description: The initial status of a newly created issue.

workflow_statuses.name: In Investigation
workflow_statuses.description: The issue is being actively investigated by an operator.

workflow_statuses.name: Awaiting Customer
workflow_statuses.description: Progress is blocked pending a response from the customer.

workflow_statuses.name: Resolved
workflow_statuses.description: The issue has been fixed and is considered complete.

roles.name: Fulfillment Specialist
roles.description: Users who manage the day-to-day processing, shipment, and troubleshooting of orders.

roles.name: Payment Analyst
roles.description: Users responsible for investigating and resolving payment verification flags and disputes.

roles.name: Project Administrator
roles.description: Users with full administrative rights over the Jira project.

screens.name: MFP: Resolve Issue Screen
screens.description: Screen displayed when an operator resolves an issue, prompting for resolution details.
